Why I want to move from Linux to OpenBSD:

1. Linux kernel file descriptor limits.
2. Linux kernel caching instead of writing.
3. Linux kernel optimizations; bloating.
4. Linux kernel bows down to proprietary hw.
5. Linux kernel bows down to proprietary sw.
6. OpenBSD philosophy: correctness, minimalism.
   Or as I like to say, perfection is nothingness.

Once OpenBSD DEs are polished, I'll use it.
